	Demonstrate design best practices for teams in the creation of user interfaces, concept&nbsp; models, user flows and interaction design schematics.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Responsibilities:</p>
<p>
	<br />
	&bull; Passion for creating exceptional experiences in the digital space<br />
	&bull; Perpetually seek to sharpen and broaden your skills<br />
	&bull; Create and validate user interfaces and experiences for multiple platforms - Web, Social Media (Facebook), Mobile (iOS, Android)<br />
	&bull; Support development on multiple platforms by maping workflows, user paths and wire frames and creating storyboards, mockups, low and high fidelity prototypes<br />
	&bull; Strong communication skills - Present work and findings&nbsp; to internal stakeholders and clients<br />
	&bull; Go through general and specific training as and when required by your manager.<br />
	&bull; Keep open and continual communications with your manager and your team with regard to workload and projects.<br />
	&bull; Work on any other reasonable task requested by your senior manager.</p>
<p>
	Key Skills: Essential:</p>
<p>
	<br />
	&bull; Solid previous UI experience - Portfolio showcasing a history of complex web interfaces and strong graphic design capabilities<br />
	&bull; Strong intuition for effective Web 2.0 style of user interfaces, focusing on uncluttered design, smart navigation and SEO-friendly content<br />
	&bull; Data driven; familiarity with key online marketing metrics like CPC, CPM, CTR etc.<br />
	&bull; Previous exposure to A/B testing or MV testing for optimizing web interfaces. Previous experience with Google Website Optimizer a major plus.<br />
	&bull; Strong in paying attention to detail and have exceptional organisation, logic and analytical skills and a passion for understanding people and interaction<br />
	&bull; Strong team working skills and ability to work alone<br />
	&bull; Clean design sense is a plus, but this is not a visual design position</p>
